news.title: Landeed raises Rs 19.5 crore in pre-seed funding round
news.para: The Bengaluru-based company plans to use the funds to expedite product development as well as build a comprehensive and standardized property documentation retrieval system.

news.title: Vacate three rickety buildings in Jogeshwari West: Bombay HC
news.para: The direction by Justices Ramesh Dhanuka and Kamal Khata was passed on a 2018 petition by 59 out of 88 tenants of Kunj Niwas that comprises three buildings of 1, 2 and 3 floors, respectively.

news.title: Hyderabad civic body inches closer to Rs 2,000 crore property tax target
news.para: According to official data, till August 2, 2022, the civic body earned 993.88 crore from 9.64 lakh property owners. The corporation has set a target of 2,000 crore for the financial year 2022-23.

news.title: Brigade Group to develop land parcels in Chennai and Bengaluru
news.para: The agreement to purchase the Mount Road property in Chennai from the TVS Group company has a potential 1 million sq ft of mixed-use development comprising office, retail and residential.

news.title: Government takes measures to control construction costs of affordable housing projects
news.para: In Union Budget 2021-22 and 2022-23, customs duty has been reduced uniformly to 7.5% on semis, flat and long products of non-alloy, alloy and stainless steels.

news.title: Visaka Industries to invest Rs 120 crore in new board plant in West Bengal
news.para: ​This will be Visaka's fifth fibre cement boards plant and the first such unit in the state. The company has one more plant in the same district for cement roof sheets.

news.title: NCLAT rejects Satra Properties plea, sends company into insolvency
news.para: Praful Nanji Satra, promoter of the listed company, had challenged a plea filed by VISTRA ITCL India with regards to the company's default on secured redeemable non-convertible debentures (NCDs) worth ₹56 crore.

news.title: Eldeco Housing and Industries' profit jumps to Rs 10 crore in Q1 FY23
news.para: Total income rose to Rs 30.07 crore in the April-June quarter of this fiscal from Rs 16.46 crore in the corresponding period of the previous year.

news.title: In New York, renters desperate as soaring rents exacerbate housing crisis
news.para: Renting in New York has long been a struggle, but recently costs have skyrocketed, jumping an average 20.4 percent in the second quarter of this year alone, according to the housing search website StreetEasy.

news.title: Chandigarh administration updates MHA on property conversion, misuse penalty
news.para: The documents were taken following detailed discussion on both issues in the lengthy meeting attended by the adviser to the administrator with MHA officials.

news.title: Amrapali project: SC tells authorities to be non-obstructive on unused FAR for funding
news.para: The court directed senior officials of Noida and Greater Noida authorities to be present in court along with their advocate on the next date of hearing to thrash out the issue on selling of FAR.

news.title: Government approves town planning schemes for Ahmedabad, Surat, Bhavnagar metropolis
news.para: The Seven town planning schemes which has been approved four preliminary TP schemes for Surat and one each preliminary TP schemes for Ahmedabad and Bhavnagar also includes one draft TP for Bavla.

news.title: Adani Properties raises Rs 800 crore from Credit Suisse
news.para: APPL, which raises finances for Adani Group companies, borrowed Rs 2,525 crore this fiscal year starting April at an average rate of 15% per annum and tenure of one to three years. All the funds were raised through zero-coupon bonds by pledging shares of SB Adani Family Trust, which holds the promoter shares of listed Adani Group companies, the people said.

news.title: Keppel Land to buy 1 million sq ft in Piramal Realty's office project for Rs 1,200 crore
news.para: Keppel Land has already signed the term sheet to acquire nearly 1 million sq ft of commercial real estate spread across a total six entire floors in this multi-tenanted tower. The transaction will exclude nearly 2 lakh sq ft office space occupied by Piramal enterprises.

news.title: Bengaluru development body vows to finish works at its layouts, but sets no deadline
news.para: The plan is to ready Anjanapura, Visvesvaraya and Banashankari 6 Stage (1, 2 blocks) layouts after completing pending civic works worth over Rs 400 crore.
